<head>Cap. CLXXV.</head>
<foreign xml:lang="grc">Σμίλαξ κηπαία</foreign> est sine haesitatione<lb/> idem genus ac <foreign xml:lang="grc">φασίολος</foreign> (c. 130.), sed alia species. E vo-<lb break="no"/>lubili enim indole et seminibus variegatis, partim rufe-<lb break="no"/>scentibus, patet, esse nostram <foreign xml:lang="grc">σμίλακα</foreign> <hi rend="italic">Phaseolum vulga-</hi><lb break="no"/><hi rend="italic">rem</hi>, seminibus variegatis, qui ex India orientali Ale-<lb break="no"/>xandri forte temporibus allatus, a Theophrasto et <foreign xml:lang="grc">δόλιχος</foreign><lb/> nominatur.<ref target="#fn36">36</ref> Eum ipsum dolichon suo aevo vel <foreign xml:lang="grc">λοβόν</foreign>,<lb/> vel <foreign xml:lang="grc">φασήολον</foreign> dici, Galenus testatur.<ref target="#fn37">37</ref> Sed probabile etiam<lb/> est, <foreign xml:lang="grc">φασιόλου</foreign> nomine notari <hi rend="italic">Phaseolum nanum</hi>. Alvo fa-<lb break="no"/>cile <foreign xml:lang="grc">δολίχους</foreign> secedere, Hippocraticus auctor docet.<ref target="#fn38">38</ref> Dio-<lb break="no"/>cles autem primus videtur <foreign xml:lang="grc">φασήλων</foreign> nomen introduxis-<lb break="no"/>se.<ref target="#fn39">39</ref> Ita <foreign xml:lang="grc">φασήλους</foreign> virides in coenis pro bellariis Laco-<lb break="no"/>nes dedisse, Polemon tradit.<ref target="#fn40">40</ref><lb/>
<head>Cap. CLXXVI.</head>
